claim.claim-text:
1. A method for making a charging electrode structure for flexible electrical connection between charging electrodes and control electronics comprising the steps of: 
electroforming an electrode structure onto a sacrificial metallic substrate; 
using a first portion of the electrode structure to form the charging electrodes and a second portion of the electrode structure to form the flexible electrical connection; 
laminating the second portion of the electrode structure to a flexible carrier film; 
laminating the first portion of the electrode structure to a rigid, dielectric substrate; and 
removing the sacrificial metallic substrate.

10. A charging electrode structure for flexible electrical connection between charging electrodes and control electronics comprising: 
an electrode structure electroformed onto a sacrificial metallic substrate, the electrode structure having a first portion to form the charging electrodes and a second portion to form the flexible electrical connection; 
means for laminating the second portion of the electrode structure to a flexible carrier film; 
means for laminating the first portion of the electrode structure to a rigid, dielectric substrate; and 
means for removing the sacrificial metallic substrate.
